events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel and No. 15 Texas A&M shook-up the national championship race by beating No. 1 Alabama 29-23 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manziel, A&M knock off No. 1 Bama

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Collin Klein, the Heisman Trophy hopeful starting a week after an apparent head injury, ran for two touchdowns for Kansas State (No. 2 BCS, No. 3 AP) in a 23-10 victory Saturday night at TCU, which is in its first season in the Big 12.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein, K-State win, boost title hopes

events.name: Oregon Ducks at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota overcame a brief injury to throw for a career-high 377 yards and tie a school record with six touchdown passes as Oregon (No. 3 BCS, No. 2 AP) made a case for the top ranking in the country by beating California 59-17,
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota's 6 TDs lead Oregon by Cal

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Everett Golson ran for a touchdown and threw for two more on Saturday night to help No. 4 Notre Dame beat Boston College 21-6 and keep its national championship hopes intact.
headlines.shortLinkText: ND bounces BC to stay unbeaten

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Aaron Murray passed for 208 yards and three touchdowns, freshman tailbacks Todd Gurley and Keith Marshall each ran for more than 100 yards and No. 5 Georgia overwhelmed Auburn 38-0 on Saturday night.

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jelani Jenkins returned a blocked punt 36 yards for a touchdown with 2 seconds remaining, and Florida rallied in the closing minutes to beat Louisiana-Lafayette 27-20 on Saturday.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Zach Mettenberger passed for 273 yards and two touchdowns, and LSU (No. 7 BCS, No. 9 AP) kept alive faint hope of a Southeastern Conference title with a 37-17 victory over Mississippi State (No. 21 BCS, No. 23 AP) on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mettenberger, LSU coast by Miss. State

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw for two touchdowns and ran for another score as South Carolina (No. 8 BCS, No. 12 AP) beat Arkansas 38-20 on Saturday.

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Ryan Nassib threw for 246 yards, Jerome Smith ran for 144 yards and Syracuse handed Louisville (No. 9 BCS, No. 11 AP) its first loss of the season in a 45-26 victory on Saturday.

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Kevin Hogan threw for 254 yards and three touchdowns in his first collegiate start, and Stanford (No. 14 BCS, No. 16 AP) overcame four turnovers to rally past Oregon State (No. 11 BCS, No. 13 AP) 27-23 on Saturday.

events.name: Baylor Bears at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw for 277 yards and two TDs, Damien Williams ran for 99 yards and two scores and Oklahoma (No. 12 BCS, No. 14 AP) beat Baylor 42-34 on Saturday to move Bob Stoops into sole possession of second place on the school's career wins list.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones throws 2 TDs as Oklahoma beats Baylor

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for 261 yards and three touchdowns in Clemson's 45-10 victory over Maryland on Saturday, the Tigers' sixth straight and record 12th in a row at Death Valley.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemson rips Maryland for 12th home win in row

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez threw a 5-yard touchdown pass to Jamal Turner for Nebraska's first lead, and the Cornhuskers overcame a double-digit, second-half deficit for the fourth time this season in a 32-23 victory over Penn State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Martinez, Huskers rally past Penn St.

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: David Ash passed for 364 yards and two touchdowns, and Texas honored former coach Darrell Royal by whipping Iowa State 33-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas honors Royal, drops Iowa St.

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Brett Hundley threw three touchdown passes to help UCLA (No. 18 BCS, No. 17 AP) beat Washington State 44-36 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA stays on roll with victory against Wazzu

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Marqise Lee caught 10 passes for 161 yards and a touchdown, Curtis McNeal rushed for 163 yards and two more scores, and Southern California bounced back from consecutive losses with a 38-17 victory over skidding Arizona State.
headlines.shortLinkText: McNeal, Lee help No. 19 Trojans bounce back

events.name: Louisiana Tech Bulldogs at Texas State Bobcats

headlines.description: No. 19 Louisiana Tech 62, Texas St. 55

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Eric Stephens took the snap out of the wildcat formation, rolled to his right and threw a 3-yard jump pass to Darrin Moore for a touchdown in double overtime to lead Texas Tech past Kansas 41-34 on Saturday.

events.name: Army Black Knights at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Brandon Coleman caught his second touchdown of the game on a 31-yard pass from Gary Nova with 8:49 to play and Rutgers (No. 23 BCS, No. 24 AP) survived a valiant effort by mistake-prone Army in posting a 28-7 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers rebounds for win over sloppy Army

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Devin Gardner ran for a 1-yard touchdown in overtime and Michigan's defense responded with a stop, giving the Wolverines a wild 38-31 win over Northwestern on Saturday.

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Montee Ball ran for 198 yards and three touchdowns, James White scored on runs of 69 and 50 yards, and Wisconsin set a school rushing record Saturday with 564 yards in a 62-14 rout at Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: Badgers' Ball 2nd on TD list after win

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Cincinnati scored on four of its last five first-half possessions and rode that momentum to a 34-10 Big East victory over Temple on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late first-half surge powers Cincinnati to victory

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Michael Rocco threw a 10-yard touchdown pass to Jake McGee with 6 seconds remaining Saturday, and Virginia rallied from a 10-point deficit to stun Miami 41-40.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia rallies from 10 down, stuns Miami late

events.name: William & Mary Tribe at Old Dominion Monarchs
Purdue Boilermakers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Paul Griggs drilled a 46-yard field goal as time expired and Purdue stunned Iowa 27-24 Saturday, snapping a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Purdue stuns Iowa late to snap 5-game skid

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Andrew Baggett kicked a 35-yard field goal in the fourth overtime period Saturday as Missouri rallied from a two-touchdown halftime deficit to beat Tennessee 51-48 at Neyland Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Missouri fights back, stuns Tennessee in 4 OTs

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Robert Godhigh rushed for two touchdowns and caught a third, and Georgia Tech held off North Carolina 68-50 on Saturday in the highest-scoring game in Atlantic Coast Conference history.

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Ka'Deem Carey ran for a Pac-12 record 366 yards and scored five touchdowns, powering Arizona to a 56-31 rout of Colorado on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zona's Carey runs for Pac-12-record 366 yards

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw two touchdown passes while Tobais Palmer returned a kickoff 100 yards for a score to help North Carolina State beat Wake Forest 37-6 on Saturday and secure bowl eligibility.

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Clint Chelf threw for 292 yards and four touchdowns in his first career start, and Josh Stewart had a career-high 172 receiving yards and scored three TDs as Oklahoma State handed West Virginia its fourth straight loss, 55-34 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chelf has 4 TDs in 1st start, propels Okla. St.

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description:
Minnesota coach Jerry Kill did it again. 
After rebuilding programs earlier in his career, Kill has the Gophers bowl eligible for the first time since 2009 after defeating Illinois 17-3 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gophers bowl eligible after getting past Illinois

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors

headlines.description: Joe Southwick threw three touchdowns and backup quarterback Grant Hedrick rushed for another and Boise State easily beat Hawaii 49-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise St. cruises past Hawaii behind Southwick

headlines.description: Jordan Rodgers hit Chris Boyd for a 26-yard touchdown pass with 52 seconds remaining and Vanderbilt rallied for a 27-26 victory over Mississippi on Saturday night.

events.name: Utah Utes at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Keith Price and Washington's offense finally broke out, with the quarterback throwing for two touchdowns and running for another, and Washington become bowl eligible for the third straight season with a 34-15 win over Utah.
headlines.shortLinkText: Price powers Washington to win against Utah
